description.plain:
Jesse Elechko, better known by his stage name Headline; is a 22 year old Canadian Hip-Hop artist hailing from Edmonton, Alberta.
 Headline grew up listening to technical lyricists and the golden-era greats.
At age 7 he taught himself how to play guitar and sing, and at age 11 he performed lead guitar for the first time at the school talent show. At 12 years of age he wrote his first rap and entered the middle school rap competition with his childhood best friend Will Turner, claiming second place.
 Since youth, Headline worked all the angles to hone and perfect his craft. Growing up with a lack of money, studio time wasn’t ever an option; so he taught himself to engineer/produce at age 14, eventually turning to engineering for much of Edmontons Hip Hop scene, and then releasing four 17 track mixtapes over the span of four years.
 Since the release of his fourth mixtape ‘All Seeing Eyez’, it has garnered over 500 thousand plays. His music has surfaced in multiple places, including but not limited to: SoundCloud Weekly, SoundCloud Stations, RapDirect, 1HipHopHub, ClubofHipHop and other media outlets. Headline has over 5000 worldwide fans across all platforms.
 He has made a name for himself as a lyricist and a songwriter. He is known for his flow, conversational content, and choice beat selection. Every Headline song ever released has been recorded, mixed and mastered by himself.

songs.title: La Noire
songs.lyrics:
Been in a jail cell, I don't wanna go back. To live a good life, that's why I rap this track. In fact this is my passion and craft. But you can never be too sure like Noah's ark. I want to do my part, to lift my dying heart. Wondering who I was all along from the start. As I go I'll figure it out. Everyone around me's trying to figure me out. Always stoned, this kid has it out for him self. He put his old self on the shelf, what's left is nothing but what he'd felt. Emotions gone like all the hands that he delt. If he's not on earth than where else?

Trying to cop a feel, for a grasp of life. Take a good look at it, never think twice. There's a reason I was put on this earth, good advice. To live an average life, it just won't suffice. So I write these raps, to clear my head. I'm only 16, I coulda been dead. But I don't wanna be dead broke. Used to starve and save my lunch money for my weekly tokes. But, I just need to focus. Cause god doesn't just shit out poets. Practice makes perfect, yeah boy you know it. I just don't want to end up soulless
But I also never wanna be smokeless and you know this
Swimming in a sea of women like a gold fish, hoping for the right one cause life's not the only bitch
Had her eye on me, a sound mind to fuck with
